pe":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Finamore was born about 1327, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Finamore, was 28 and his mother, Mrs. Thomas Finamore, was 24. He had at least 1 son with Mrs William Finamore."},"et":{"Abt 1327–":"umbes 1327–Surnud","1327–Male":"1327–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1305":"1305","1327":"1327","Abt 1350":"umbes 1350","1300":"1300","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","Abt 1327":"umbes 1327","Fenne,Devon,Eng":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1327–":"noin 1327–Kuollut","1327–Male":"1327–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1305–Female":"1305–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1327":"1327","Abt 1350":"noin 1350","1300":"1300","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","Abt 1327":"noin 1327","Fenne,Devon,Eng":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1327–":"environ 1327–Décédé","1327–Male":"1327–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","1350–Male":"1350–Décédé","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1305–Female":"1305–Décédée","1305":"1305","1327":"1327","Abt 1350":"environ 1350","1300":"1300","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","Abt 1327":"environ 1327","Fenne,Devon,Eng":"Devon,